--- !u!114 &7271954077116309683
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 5230392957894290831}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: fbeb6d65be27d3b40a131a1e4ace56b5, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  steps:
  - message: '{player}, notice how the ship trembles?'
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 0
    startTime: 0
    endTime: 0
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: Yes, Gizmo what's happening?
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: a80ac0751277f424ca977c804190eff8, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 0
    startTime: 0
    endTime: 0
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: "That\u2019s periodic motion\u2014It means a movement that happens again
      and again in a regular pattern. "
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 0
    endTime: 1
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: So this endless vibration is like the ship dancing in rhythm?
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: a80ac0751277f424ca977c804190eff8, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 1
    endTime: 2
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: Exactly! The period (T) It is the time taken for a motion to repeat
      itself, measuring one full cycle around its central point.
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 3
    endTime: 4
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: So if the cycle is faster, what happens to frequency?
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: a80ac0751277f424ca977c804190eff8, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 4
    endTime: 5
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: Frequency (f) Is defined to be the number of events per unit of time.
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 6
    endTime: 7
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: That means a short period gives a high frequency, right?
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: a80ac0751277f424ca977c804190eff8, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 7
    endTime: 8
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: "Correct! Now look here\u2014our oscillations follow Hooke\u2019s Law:
      It is objects attached to a spring or any elastic object with negligible mass."
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 9
    endTime: 10
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: So, the farther it stretches, the stronger it pulls back. That explains
      the shaking!
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: a80ac0751277f424ca977c804190eff8, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 10
    endTime: 11
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: "Right. Springs like these undergo harmonic motion and obey Hooke\u2019s
      Law perfectly."
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 0
    startTime: 0
    endTime: 0
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: Pendulums work that way too?
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: a80ac0751277f424ca977c804190eff8, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 0
    startTime: 0
    endTime: 0
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: Yes. A pendulum is objects rotate back and forth between two angular
      positions.
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 12
    endTime: 13
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: And what about different kinds of pendulums?
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: a80ac0751277f424ca977c804190eff8, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 13
    endTime: 14
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: A simple pendulum is a system consist of a particle of mass suspended
      from one end of a massless string of fixed length.
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 14
    endTime: 16
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: A physical pendulum has two pivots it is a simple pendulum. The first
      pivot the main and the second is located at the pendulum center of mass.
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 17.5
    endTime: 18
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: A torsion pendulum is a pendulum that twist back and forth, creating
      an angular harmonic motion.
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 20.5
    endTime: 21
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: Springs are the objects that undergo Hooke's Law. Its undergo angular
      harmonic motion.
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 23
    endTime: 24
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: "Thanks, Gizmo. I finally understand how everything moves in rhythm\u2014from
      springs to pendulums."
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: a80ac0751277f424ca977c804190eff8, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 1
    startTime: 25
    endTime: 26
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: "Well done, {player}. Understanding periodic motion keeps our ship\u2014and
      your knowledge\u2014in balance."
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 6a96359884e70134880e3323cd90c5eb, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 0
    startTime: 0
    endTime: 0
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
  - message: "Then I\u2019m ready for the next step. Time to prepare for the quiz!"
    character: {fileID: 11400000, guid: a80ac0751277f424ca977c804190eff8, type: 2}
    dontUseTTS: 0
    useAnimation: 0
    startTime: 0
    endTime: 0
    dialogueCondition: {fileID: 0}
